  "body": "### Overview\r\n\r\nI'm trying to use Brownie with vanilla Geth v1.10 and transactions abort with:\r\n\r\n> only replay-protected (EIP-155) transactions allowed over RPC\r\n\r\n### Specification\r\n\r\nIt looks like EIP-155 demands to have the chainId included into the tx/signature. Brownie should probably do that.\r\n\r\n### Dependencies\r\n\r\n* See section \"ChainID enforcement\" in https://blog.ethereum.org/2021/03/03/geth-v1-10-0/\r\n\r\n### Workaround\r\n\r\n* Use geth with `--rpc.allow-unprotected-txs`",
